chore: Update .env.example with placeholder values for database and Stack Auth configuration
- Replaced sensitive database URL and Stack Auth keys with placeholder values for better security practices. - Ensured clarity for developers setting up their local environment by providing clear instructions on required values.
fix(ci): Resolve security audit and lockfile issues

Update dependencies in bun.lock and package.json for improved functionality and security
- Bump versions for lucide-react, react-day-picker, and eslint-plugin-unused-imports to their latest releases. - Add a new script for security auditing in package.json to enhance project security practices. - Ensure consistent dependency management across the project.

Implement conditional Stack Auth configuration and improve error handling
- Added checks for Stack Auth configuration in layout and handler components. - Provided fallback UI when Stack Auth is not configured, enhancing user experience during CI builds. - Updated Stack Auth initialization to include a mock implementation for environments without configuration, ensuring robust error handling.

chore: enhance CI/CD workflows and golangci-lint configuration
- Update .golangci.yml to improve linter settings and enable additional checks for better code quality. - Refactor CI workflow to include a dedicated module validation job, ensuring go.mod and go.sum are up to date. - Enhance test job to run on multiple Go versions and include coverage checks. - Improve linting job with additional static analysis tools and checks for code formatting and inefficiencies. - Streamline build job to support cross-platform builds and upload artifacts with proper naming conventions.

footer.span: These metrics do not include all private contributions
